				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">This is my generic collision test routine I used in DABG and Sliding Blaster that return whether or not a collision occured in carry (for ca65, but easily adaptable to other things):<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">.macro swapa mema, memb<br />&nbsp; lda mema<br />&nbsp; pha<br />&nbsp; lda memb<br />&nbsp; sta mema<br />&nbsp; pla<br />&nbsp; sta memb<br />.endmacro<br /><br />.proc ChkTouchGeneric<br />&nbsp; jsr TryCollide<br />&nbsp; swapa TouchLeftA,&nbsp; &nbsp;TouchLeftB<br />&nbsp; swapa TouchTopA,&nbsp; &nbsp; TouchTopB<br />&nbsp; swapa TouchWidthA,&nbsp; TouchWidthB<br />&nbsp; swapa TouchHeightA, TouchHeightB<br />&nbsp; jsr TryCollide<br />&nbsp; clc ; no collision<br />&nbsp; rts<br />TryCollide:<br />&nbsp; lda TouchLeftB<br />&nbsp; clc<br />&nbsp; adc TouchWidthB<br />&nbsp; sta TouchRight<br />&nbsp; lda TouchTopB<br />&nbsp; clc<br />&nbsp; adc TouchHeightB<br />&nbsp; sta TouchBottom<br /><br />&nbsp; lda TouchLeftA<br />&nbsp; cmp TouchLeftB<br />&nbsp; bcc No<br /><br />&nbsp; lda TouchLeftA<br />&nbsp; cmp TouchRight<br />&nbsp; bcs No<br /><br />&nbsp; lda TouchTopA<br />&nbsp; cmp TouchTopB<br />&nbsp; bcc No<br /><br />&nbsp; lda TouchTopA<br />&nbsp; cmp TouchBottom<br />&nbsp; bcs No<br />&nbsp; pla ; pop the return address from either JSR off the stack<br />&nbsp; pla<br />&nbsp; sec ; collision detected<br />No:<br />&nbsp; rts<br />.endproc<br /></div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

